messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

- Full HTTP request path:
  /printdocument

- All HTTP methods acceptable:
  No

  No

  Yes

  No

- TRACE:
  No

- GET:
  No

- PUT:
  No

- DELETE:
  No

- PATCH:
  No

Explanation:
- The controller method handling this endpoint is annotated with @RequestMapping(value = "/printdocument", method = RequestMethod.POST). That explicitly maps only POST requests to the path "/printdocument".
- The controller class has no class-level @RequestMapping, so there is no additional prefix â€” the full path is exactly "/printdocument".
- No other mappings for this exact path are present in the code, and no other HTTP methods are declared for this path. Per your instruction to base acceptability on the code (not runtime framework behavior), I did not treat Spring's automatic handling of HEAD/OPTIONS as indicating those methods are acceptable unless explicitly declared.
- Note: the same controller also defines other endpoints under /printdocument (e.g., GET /printdocument/{id} and POST /printdocument/{id}/budget), but those are distinct paths and do not change the mapping for "/printdocument".
